P)\n* [[Quiet Riot]] \u2013 ''[[Metal Health]]''\n* Rage (UK) \u2013 ''Run for the Night''\n* [[Raven_(British_band)|Raven]] \u2013 ''[[All_for_One_(Raven_album)|All for One]]''\n* [[Ratt]] \u2013 ''[[Ratt (EP)|Ratt]]'' (EP)\n* Riff Raff \u2013 ''Give the Dead Man Some Water''\n* [[Riot (band)|Riot]] \u2013 ''[[Born in America]]''\n* Roadrunner - ''Teenage Warcry'' (EP)\n* [[Rock Goddess]] \u2013 ''[[Rock Goddess (album)|Rock Goddess]]''\n* Rock Goddess \u2013 ''[[Hell Hath No Fury (Rock Goddess album)|Hell Hath No Fury]]''\n* [[The Rods]] \u2013 ''In the Raw''\n* The Rods \u2013 ''Live'' (live)\n* [[Satan (band)|Satan]] \u2013 ''Court in the Act''\n* Satan Jokers \u2013 ''Les Fils du M\u00e9tal''\n* [[Savage (band)|Savage]] \u2013 ''Loose 'N Lethal''\n* [[Savage Grace (metal band)|Savage Grace]] \u2013 ''The Dominatress'' (EP)\n* [[Savatage]] \u2013 ''[[Sirens (Savatage album)|Sirens]]''\n* [[Saxon (band)|Saxon]] \u2013 ''[[Power & the Glory]]''\n* [[Shy (band)|Shy]] \u2013 ''Once Bitten... Twice...''\n* Silver Mountain \u2013 ''Shakin' Brains''\n* [[Sinner (band)|Sinner]] \u2013 ''Fast Decision''\n* Six Feet Under (Swe) \u2013 ''Six Feet Under''\n* [[S.A.Slayer|Slayer]] (S.A.Slayer) \u2013 ''Prepare to Die'' (EP)\n* [[Slayer]] \u2013 ''[[Show No Mercy (Slayer album)|Show No Mercy]]''\n* Sledgehammer \u2013 ''Blood on Their Hands''\n* [[Sortil\u00e8ge (band)|Sortil\u00e8ge]] \u2013 ''[[Sortil\u00e8ge (EP)|Sortil\u00e8ge]]'' (EP)\n* [[Sound Barrier]] \u2013 ''Total Control''\n* Spartan Warrior \u2013 ''Steel n' Chains''\n* [[Stampede (band)|Stampede]] \u2013 ''Hurricane Town''\n* [[Starfighters (band)|Starfighters]] \u2013 ''In-Flight Movie''\n* [[Steeler (American band)|Steeler]] \u2013 ''[[Steeler (American album)|Steeler]]''\n* [[Suicidal Tendencies]] \u2013 ''[[Suicidal Tendencies (album)|Suicidal Tendencies]]''\n* Takashi \u2013 ''Kamikaze Killers'' (EP)\n* [[Talas (band)#Talas|Talas]] \u2013 ''Live Speed on Ice'' \n* [[Terraplane (band)|Terraplane]]  \u2013  ''I Survive'' (EP)\n* [[Thin Lizzy]] \u2013 ''[[Thunder and Lightning (album)|Thunder and Lightning]]''\n* Thin Lizzy \u2013 ''[[Life (Thin Lizzy album)|Life - Live]]''\n* [[Thunderstick]] \u2013 ''Feel Like Rock\u00b4n\u00b4Roll?'' (EP)\n* [[Tokyo Blade]] \u2013 ''[[Tokyo Blade (album)|Tokyo Blade]]''\n* Torch \u2013 ''Torch''\n* [[Bernie Torm\u00e9]] \u2013 ''Electric Gypsies''\n* [[Trance (band)|Trance]] \u2013 ''Power Infusion''\n* [[Triumph (band)|Triumph]] \u2013 ''[[Never Surrender (Triumph album)|Never Surrender]]''\n* [[Twisted Sister]] \u2013 ''[[You Can't Stop Rock 'n' Roll]]''\n* [[220 Volt (band)|220 Volt]] \u2013 ''220 Volt''\n* [[UFO (band)|UFO]] \u2013 ''[[Making Contact (album)|Making Contact]]''\n* [[Vanadium (band)|Vanadium]] \u2013 ''A Race with the Devil''\n* [[Vandenberg (band)|Vandenberg]] \u2013 ''[[Heading for a Storm]]''\n* [[Vardis]] \u2013 ''The Lion's Share'' (comp)\n* Victim \u2013 ''Power Hungry'' \n* [[Virgin Steele]] \u2013 ''[[Guardians of the Flame (album)|Guardians of the Flame]]''\n* Virgin Steele \u2013 ''[[Wait for the Night]]'' (EP)\n* [[Hawaii (band)|Vixen]] \u2013 ''Made in Hawaii'' (EP)\n* [[Warlord (band)|Warlord]] \u2013 ''Deliver Us'' (EP)\n* [[Warriors (band)|Warriors]] \u2013 ''[[Warriors (1983 Warriors album)|Warriors]]''\n* [[Wild Dogs]] \u2013 ''Wild Dogs''\n* Wildfire \u2013 ''Brute Force and Ignorance''\n* Winterkat \u2013 ''Winterkat'' (EP)\n* [[Witchfinder General (band)|Witchfinder General]] \u2013 ''[[Friends of Hell]]''\n* [[Witchfynde]] \u2013 ''Cloak and Dagger''\n* [[Mark Slaughter|Xcursion]] \u2013 ''Xcursion'' (EP)\n* [[Y&T]] \u2013 ''[[Mean Streak (album)|Mean Streak]]''\n* [[Zebra (American band)|Zebra]] \u2013 ''[[Zebra (Zebra album)|Zebra]]''\n* Zero Nine \u2013 ''Headline''\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Events==\n* [[Yngwie Malmsteen]] starts performing in the band [[Steeler (American band)|Steeler]]. Also in that band was vocalist [[Ron Keel]] (later on [[Keel (band)|Keel]]) and former [[W.A.S.P. (band)|W.A.S.P.]] bassist Rik Fox. The band produced only one album, ''[[Steeler (American album)|Steeler]]''.\n* [[Dave Mustaine]], lead guitarist for [[Metallica]], is fired for drug/alcohol abuse, and is replaced by [[Exodus (band)|Exodus]] guitarist [[Kirk Hammett]], after which he forms the L.A. [[thrash metal]] band [[Megadeth]].\n* [[Kiss (band)|KISS]] ended the use of makeup in their act.\n* November 19: the single by [[Quiet Riot]] \"[[Cum on Feel the Noize]]\" is No. 5 on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100.\n* April 17: [[Mountain (band)|Mountain]] bassist, and [[Cream (band)|Cream]] producer, [[Felix Pappalardi]] was shot and killed by his wife [[Gail Collins Pappalardi]].\n* [[Metallica]] and [[Slayer]] both release their debut albums ''[[Kill 'Em All]]'' and ''[[Show No Mercy (Slayer album)|Show No Mercy]]''.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{Timeline box|title=[[Timeline of heavy metal music|Heavy Metal Timeline]]|before=[[1982 in heavy metal music|1982]]|after=[[1984 in heavy metal music|1984]]|year='''1983'''}}\n{{S-end}}\n{{Timeline of heavy metal and hard rock music}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:1983 In Heavy Metal Music}}\n[[Category:1980s in heavy metal music]]\n[[Category:1983 in music|Metal]]\n", "text_old": "{{Year in music|1983}}\n{{Year nav topic5|1983|heavy metal music}}\n\n{{unref|date=February 2015}}This is a timeline documenting the events of [[Heavy Metal music|heavy metal]] in 1983.\n\n==Newly formed bands==\n* [[Alcatrazz]]\n* [[Autograph (American band)|Autograph]]\n*[[Bad Steve]]\n* [[Bathory (band)|Bathory]]\n* [[Bon Jovi]]\n* [[Carnivore (band)|Carnivore]]\n* [[Child's Play (band)|Child'\u01a8 Play]]\n*[[Coroner (band)|Coroner]]\n*[[Darxon]]\n* [[Death (metal band)|Death]]\n*[[Elixir (British band)|Elixir]] \n* [[Excel (band)|Excel]] (known as Chaotic Noise until 1985)\n* [[Fastway (band)|Fastway]]\n* [[Hagar Schon Aaronson Shrieve]]\n*[[Impaler (band)|Impaler]] \n*[[Kab\u00e1t]]\n*[[Korzus]]\n*[[Lizzy Borden (band)|Lizzy Borden]]\n* [[Master (American band)|Master]]\n* [[Megadeth]]\n*[[Melvins]]\n* [[Morbid Angel]]\n* [[Necrophagia]]\n*[[Omen (band)|Omen]] \n* [[Poison (American band)|Poison]]\n* [[Possessed (band)|Possessed]]\n*[[Razor (band)|Razor]] \n* [[Rigor Mortis (band)|Rigor Mortis]]\n*[[Rogue Male (band)|Rogue Male]]\n*[[Sacrifice (band)|Sacrifice]]\n* [[Stryper]]\n* [[Testament (band)|Testament]] (known as Legacy until 1986)\n* [[Vader (band)|Vader]]\n*[[Warrant (German band)|Warrant]] \n* [[White Lion]]\n\n==Albums & EPs==\n{{Div col|colwidth=20em}}\n* [[AC/DC]] \u2013 ''[[Flick of the Switch]]''\n* [[Accept (band)|Accept]] \u2013 ''[[Balls to the Wall]]''\n* Ace Lane \u2013 ''See You In Heaven''\n* Acid \u2013 ''Maniac''\n* [[Alcatrazz]] \u2013 ''[[No Parole from Rock N' Roll]]''\n* [[Alice Cooper]] \u2013 ''[[DaDa]]''\n* Alien (US) \u2013 ''Cosmic Fantasy'' (EP)\n* [[The Angels (Australian band)|The Angels]], aka Angel City \u2013 ''[[Watch the Red]]''\n* [[Anvil (band)|Anvil]] \u2013 ''[[Forged in Fire]]''\n* Argus - ''Argus'' (EP)\n* [[Armored Saint]] \u2013 ''[[Armored Saint (EP)|Armored Saint]]'' (EP)\n* Ashbury \u2013 ''Endless Skies''\n* [[Atomic Rooster]] \u2013 '''[[Headline News (album)|Headline News]]''\n* [[Axewitch|Axe Witch]] - ''[[The Lord of Flies]]'' \n* [[Bar\u00f3n Rojo]] \u2013 ''[[Metalmorfosis]]''\n* [[Battleaxe (band)|Battleaxe]] \u2013 ''Burn This Town''\n* [[Billy Idol]] - ''[[Rebel Yell (album)|Rebel Yell]]''\n* [[Bitch (band)|Bitch]] \u2013 ''[[Be My Slave]]''\n* Bitches Sin \u2013  ''No More Chances'' (EP)\n* Black Angels \u2013 ''Kickdown''\n* [[Blackfoot (band)|Blackfoot]] \u2013 ''[[Siogo]]''\n* [[Black Sabbath]] \u2013 ''[[Born Again (Black Sabbath album)|Born Again]]''\n* [[Blue \u00d6yster Cult]] \u2013 ''[[The Rev\u00f6lution by Night]]''\n* [[Bodine (band)|Bodine]] \u2013 ''Three Times Running''\n* [[Bow Wow (band)|Bow Wow]] \u2013 ''Holy Expedition - Live''\n* Bullet (Ger) \u2013 ''No Mercy''\n* [[Chateaux (band)|Chateaux]] \u2013 ''Chained and Desperate''\n*