 for a Storm]]''\n* [[Vardis]] \u2013 ''The Lion's Share'' (comp)\n* Victim \u2013 ''Power Hungry'' \n* [[Virgin Steele]] \u2013 ''[[Guardians of the Flame (album)|Guardians of the Flame]]''\n* Virgin Steele \u2013 ''[[Wait for the Night]]'' (EP)\n* [[Hawaii (band)|Vixen]] \u2013 ''Made in Hawaii'' (EP)\n* [[Warlord (band)|Warlord]] \u2013 ''Deliver Us'' (EP)\n* [[Warriors (band)|Warriors]] \u2013 ''[[Warriors (1983 Warriors album)|Warriors]]''\n* [[Wild Dogs]] \u2013 ''Wild Dogs''\n* Wildfire \u2013 ''Brute Force and Ignorance''\n* Winterkat \u2013 ''Winterkat'' (EP)\n* [[Witchfinder General (band)|Witchfinder General]] \u2013 ''[[Friends of Hell]]''\n* [[Witchfynde]] \u2013 ''Cloak and Dagger''\n* [[Mark Slaughter|Xcursion]] \u2013 ''Xcursion'' (EP)\n* [[Y&T]] \u2013 ''[[Mean Streak (album)|Mean Streak]]''\n* [[Zebra (American band)|Zebra]] \u2013 ''[[Zebra (Zebra album)|Zebra]]''\n* Zero Nine \u2013 ''Headline''\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Events==\n* [[Yngwie Malmsteen]] starts performing in the band [[Steeler (American band)|Steeler]]. Also in that band was vocalist [[Ron Keel]] (later on [[Keel (band)|Keel]]) and former [[W.A.S.P. (band)|W.A.S.P.]] bassist Rik Fox. The band produced only one album, ''[[Steeler (American album)|Steeler]]''.\n* [[Dave Mustaine]], lead guitarist for [[Metallica]], is fired for drug/alcohol abuse, and is replaced by [[Exodus (band)|Exodus]] guitarist [[Kirk Hammett]], after which he forms the L.A. [[thrash metal]] band [[Megadeth]].\n* [[Kiss (band)|KISS]] ended the use of makeup in their act.\n* November 19: the single by [[Quiet Riot]] \"[[Cum on Feel the Noize]]\" is No. 5 on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100.\n* April 17: [[Mountain (band)|Mountain]] bassist, and [[Cream (band)|Cream]] producer, [[Felix Pappalardi]] was shot and killed by his wife [[Gail Collins Pappalardi]].\n* [[Metallica]] and [[Slayer]] both release their debut albums ''[[Kill 'Em All]]'' and ''[[Show No Mercy (Slayer album)|Show No Mercy]]''.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{Timeline box|title=[[Timeline of heavy metal music|Heavy Metal Timeline]]|before=[[1982 in heavy metal music|1982]]|after=[[1984 in heavy metal music|1984]]|year='''1983'''}}\n{{S-end}}\n{{Timeline of heavy metal and hard rock music}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:1983 In Heavy Metal Music}}\n[[Category:1980s in heavy metal music]]\n[[Category:1983 in music|Metal]]\n", "name_user": "Metalmaniac87", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eNewly formed bands", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1983_in_heavy_metal_music"}
